 {"id":"bd-yx9r.5.4","title":"Port observability, monitor, evidence, and evidence-sink public parity","description":"The reopened backlog still underrepresented upstream observability and monitoring surfaces: monitor.rs, evidence.rs, evidence_sink.rs, and the broader observability story promised by the crate. ANSI C cannot claim user-facing parity if proof collection and runtime observability remain hidden inside ad hoc diagnostics.","design":"Implement public observability, monitor, evidence, and evidence-sink modules that collect structured diagnostic material, integrate with trace/runtime state, and feed both operator reports and deterministic failure artifacts. This bead should be explicit about detailed logging, artifact schema, and verdict derivation so future users can trust the output.","acceptance_criteria":"A. Public monitor/observability/evidence/evidence-sink modules exist with coherent contracts.\\nB. Unit tests cover evidence accumulation, monitor thresholding, verdict aggregation, and negative/error paths.\\nC. At least one logged e2e lane emits rich evidence artifacts and human-readable summaries that a maintainer can use without reproducing the failure immediately.","notes":"Primary upstream references: src/monitor.rs, src/evidence.rs, src/evidence_sink.rs, and observability exports in src/lib.rs. Coordinate closely with bd-yx9r.3 and bd-yx9r.6.2 so artifact formats stay consistent.","status":"in_progress","priority":1,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-03-13T22:27:51.773247510Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-03-14T22:59:45.690683053Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["crate-parity","evidence","monitor","observability"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"bd-yx9r.5.4","depends_on_id":"bd-yx9r.1","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-13T22:28:08.165983935Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-yx9r.5.4","depends_on_id":"bd-yx9r.2","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-13T22:28